                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34532/12–445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-04T17:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 4, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 4—4:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3603. Now that Kidd<note n="59" xml:id="d489fn59">Philip C. Kidd, Field
                        Commissioner for Latin America, Office of Foreign Liquidation Commission,
                        Department of State.</note> is here with full authority to liquidate
                    surplus, Dept. may wish to inquire about status of U.S. naval operating base in
                    Rio. It was left here nominally to complete “rollup” program, that is liquidate
                    odds and ends. It has here more than 50 officers and 200 enlisted men and good
                    many of officers seem not to have anything to do. Possibly discreet inquiry of
                    Navy as to their policy in this regard would be useful in getting it brought to
                    logical proportion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
